title: S.J. boys and girls: Haddonfield's Gess blazes at Eastern States
text:
Olympic Conference. Megan Reardigan's first-half goal proved to be the winner for host Paul VI in a 1-0 defeat of Camden Catholic. Rylee Milligan recorded the shutout.
Nonleague. Taylor Perkowski scored two goals, and Collingswood won, 4-0, at Pennsauken. Boys' Soccer Tyler Kraft scored with three seconds left in the second overtime period, and Triton beat visiting Clearview, 3-2, in Tri-County Royal play. Javiar Arias and Shane Hartey also scored.
Burlington County. Matt Hannan, Tyler Kazmierowicz, and Chris Scoglio each had a goal in Rancocas Valley's 3-1 win at Delran. Luis Rivadeneira had two assists. 
Colonial Conference. Jack Dugan had two goals and two assists to lead host Haddonfield to a 5-0 win over Haddon Heights. Field Hockey Claudia Bowman and Maddy Raws each had a goal to give host Haddon Heights a 2-0 win over Triton in nonleague play.
Meghan Smart scored four goals to power Haddonfield to a 5-0 home win against Seneca. 
Olympic Conference. Brooke Wasco recorded seven saves for host Cherokee in a 3-0 win over Lenape. Vic Rawden, Brooke Yarsinsky, and Christina Orio each scored.
